text.section:
It is the policy of the Commonwealth that a comprehensive and integrated waste management system to handle solid waste is to be fostered. State policies and funding assistance shall reflect a preference for projects and practices consistent with the policies and goals established by this section and the following:
Education of the citizens of the Commonwealth regarding proper disposal of waste;
Collection and proper disposal of all of solid waste for proper management;
Elimination of illegal dumps throughout the Commonwealth; and
Abatement of litter on state and county rights-of-way.
